name, your mother's name, and how your father was

00:34.963 --> 00:40.650
employed? Well, my father was a sailor aboard a 
sailing ship. When he left home, his mother

00:46.977 --> 00:58.430
remarried, and he was kind of forced out of the 
home, and he went as a cabin boy of the old days of the

00:46.977 --> 00:58.430
sailing ships and did quite a bit of sailing. Then 
he came ashore.

01:02.418 --> 01:07.364
and got a job packing boxes in the shipping 
department. He was in that. Where was this? In New

01:09.286 --> 01:10.167
York City. New York City. And what was his full 
name? James McCrossin Lindsey. And your mother's

01:17.435 --> 01:18.216
name? Ida Augusta Tucker was her maiden name. 
Lindsey was her last name. Can you tell us? She grew

01:27.726 --> 01:30.990
up in New York, Brooklyn, New York. Tell us a little 
bit about your boyhood days in New York. Well, it

01:36.832 --> 01:39.635
was a country town when I was there.

01:45.301 --> 02:01.838
One of the boys' radio was just coming in, and there 
was an older boy around the neighborhood that was

01:45.301 --> 02:01.838
interested, and he built his own radio receiving 
set, and I got so I could read the code, and that is

02:02.476 --> 02:06.643
